// nodule: std.dense
// `std.dense` ‚Äî Ring 1 / Tier A capability surface (M-518; RFC-0016 ¬ß4.1).
//
// An ergonomic, value-semantic surface over [`mycelium_dense`] (M-230) typed, dimension-tracked
// dense values (`Dense{dim, dtype}` tensors / embeddings). `dim` and `dtype` are carried in the
// [`DenseSpace`] descriptor so a shape or precision mismatch is an explicit typed error, never a
// silent broadcast, truncation, or re-round (C1/G2).
//
// ## Contract (RFC-0016 ¬ß4.1 C1‚ÄìC6)
//
// - **C1 ‚Äî never-silent:** dim/dtype mismatch ‚Üí [`StdDenseError`]; zero-norm cosine ‚Üí explicit
//   `Err(ZeroNorm)`; off-grid / wrong-length input ‚Üí explicit `Err`; no `NaN`/sentinel escapes.
// - **C2 ‚Äî honest per-op tag:** integer ops ‚Üí `Exact`; float **elementwise** (`add`/`sub`/`scale`/
//   `hadamard`) ‚Üí `Proven` (Q1 ‚Äî finalized: the ADR-010 per-element IEEE backward-error
//   instantiation, M-512 delivered); float **accumulation** (`sum`/`dot`/`l1_norm`) ‚Üí `Empirical`
//   (the `nŒ≥_n` bound is a distinct theorem, not yet checked); `l2_norm`/`cosine` ‚Üí `Empirical`
//   (FLAG Q2 ‚Äî sqrt/division composition side-conditions not yet fully checked; honest downgrade
//   per VR-5). Tags degrade by meet; never upgrade without a checked basis.
// - **C3 ‚Äî EXPLAIN:** every float result carries a reified [`OpBound`] (Œµ, norm, basis string),
//   inspectable without further processing. A `from_slice` or `cosine` failure names which check
//   failed.
// - **C4 ‚Äî value-semantic:** all ops are pure functions; `Dense` values are immutable.
// - **C5 ‚Äî above the kernel (KC-3):** consumes `mycelium-dense` + `mycelium-core`; no new trusted
//   code, no `unsafe`, no FFI.
// - **C6 ‚Äî declared effects:** every op here is pure (`effects: none`) except `map`, whose effects
//   are its function argument's declared effects only.
//
// ## Guarantee matrix (RFC-0016 ¬ß4.5 ‚Äî encoded as data, asserted in tests)
//
// See [`GUARANTEE_MATRIX`] and the `guarantee_matrix_*` tests.
//
// ## Scope boundary
//
// - Representation changes (`Dense{F32}‚ÜíDense{BF16}`, `Dense‚ÜîVSA`) ‚Üí **`std.swap`** (M-516).
// - The Œµ/Œ¥ bound algebra ‚Üí **`std.numerics`** (M-512; ADR-010); this module *consumes*, never
//   defines.
// - Non-representation scalar conversion ‚Üí **`std.cmp`/`convert`** (M-532).
// - VSA hypervector algebra ‚Üí **`std.vsa`** (M-513).
//
// ## Q1 (RESOLVED for elementwise; accumulation stays `Empirical`) ‚Äî float `Proven` disposition
//
// The `Proven` tags on `add`/`sub`/`scale`/`hadamard` (float DT) are **finalized** (DN-16,
// 2026-06-19; maintainer-ratified): they rest on the ADR-010 `ErrorBound` per-element IEEE
// backward-error instantiation (`fl(a‚àòb) = (a‚àòb)(1+Œ¥)`, `|Œ¥| ‚â§ u` ‚Äî Higham 2002, Thm 2.2), whose
// single side-condition (operand finiteness / no overflow) is **guarded at runtime** (non-finite
// inputs ‚Üí kernel [`DenseError::NonFinite`], surfaced as [`StdDenseError::Kernel`]) and re-validated
// by the numerics checker (M-512, delivered).
// The accumulation ops (`sum`, `dot`, `l1_norm`) stay **`Empirical`** conservatively: the `nŒ≥_n`
// accumulation bound is a *distinct* theorem not yet discharged by a checked instantiation;
// upgrade accumulation to `Proven` only when that checked accumulation theorem is delivered (VR-5).
//
// ## FLAG Q2 ‚Äî `Empirical` for l2_norm / cosine
//
// `l2_norm` and `cosine` compose a bounded dot/sum-of-squares with a sqrt (and cosine adds a
// division). The composed bound's side-conditions are guarded at runtime (`ZeroNorm` for cosine)
// but **not yet fully checkable** through the ADR-010 affine/error kernel. Tagged `Empirical`
// pending a checked composition from M-512. Upgrade requires a checked theorem (VR-5).
//
// ## FLAG Q3 ‚Äî integer dtype ops (design claims; kernel pending)
//
// The v1 `mycelium-dense` supports only `F32`/`BF16`; integer dtype ops are specified in the
// guarantee matrix as `Exact` design claims but are not implemented in the underlying kernel
// (M-230 v1 scope, FLAG Q3). They will be implemented when the kernel adds integer dtype support.
//
// ## Ambient Representation (RFC-0012 ¬ß8-Q3)
//
// This crate's public API participates in the RFC-0012 ambient-representation contract:
// the representation choice (binary/ternary/dense/VSA) is implicit at the call site but
// always reified, queryable, and EXPLAIN-able ‚Äî never a black box (C3/SC-3).
// [Declared per RFC-0012; direction accepted in DN-07 ¬ß8-Q3; per-ring pass scheduled as M-540.]
//
// **For this crate (Ring 1, Tier A):** Dense operations always operate in the `Dense`
// representation; no implicit cross-representation conversion occurs. Shape and dtype are carried
// in the [`DenseSpace`] descriptor (never inferred), and a shape or dtype mismatch is an explicit
// `Err`, never a silent broadcast or re-round (C1). Representation changes (`Dense{F32}‚ÜíDense{BF16}`,
// `Dense‚ÜîVSA`) are explicit swaps in `std.swap` ‚Äî never automatic.
//
// # Stability (DN-66 freeze, 2026-07-01)
//
// This crate's public API, as documented in `docs/spec/stdlib/dense.md` (spec status:
// Accepted (2026-06-20)) and asserted by its guarantee-matrix table, is the **frozen baseline** per
// [DN-66](../../../docs/notes/DN-66-Stdlib-Stable-API-Freeze-And-Rust-Crate-Retirement-Status.md).
// A future breaking change here needs a spec amendment + changelog entry, not a silent edit (G2).
// It remains the RFC-0031 D6 differential-oracle reference; no `.myc` port of this module exists yet, so the D6 retirement trigger has not fired and no item here is `#[deprecated]`.
// @summary: best-effort transpilation via mycelium-transpile (M-873). Declared,
// unvalidated ‚Äî no Mycelium parser/typechecker confirms this output; see the
// accompanying .gap.json for every construct this pass could not express.
nodule std.dense;

// The citation string for element-wise `Proven` bounds (add/sub/scale/hadamard).
fn elementwise_citation(dtype: ScalarKind) => Bytes = match dtype { Bf16 => to_owned("two-rounding composition (1+Œ¥‚ÇÅ)(1+Œ¥‚ÇÇ)‚àí1 ‚â§ 2^‚àí8 + 2^‚àí23: native f32 op then bfloat16 round-to-nearest ‚Äî Higham (2002), Thm 2.2; side-conditions checked per element (Q1 finalized; M-512-checked)"), _ => to_owned("round-to-nearest relative error ‚â§ u = 2^‚àí24 for IEEE binary32 ‚Äî Higham (2002), Thm 2.2; side-conditions checked per element (Q1 finalized; M-512-checked)") };
